1. Which of the following is not one of the essential parts of a use case?
Ans: user story

2. An actor in a use case is anything with behavior who lives outside of the system we are designing,
  but has a goal they want to accomplish within.
Ans: True

3. When writing a scenario for a use case, you should focus on the actor's goal,
  the user's intention using active voice, and finally writing succinct descriptions
  of the scenario.
Ans: True

4. In a Knowledge Bas use case where title may include Sear Articles, View
  Articles, Manage Users, Create Articles, and View Analytics. The actor Contributor
  can be linked to which of the following title?
Ans: Create Article title
